<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="59" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="59">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="59">
The thorax is typically partly red in most specimens; however melanic forms are occasionally found. The specimens collected here are entirely black but agree in all structural features with the red form. Colour variation is common in some 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="4" pageNumber="59" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Perreyiinae">Perreyiinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
